<br>
     If I were a GM of a guild who's prime time was 1pm to 9pm central, and I were trying to maximize kills after a patch, I'd leave one or two rotation mobs up and chase others. Knowing my guild is going to be able to set up 6 hours ahead of the ones who's main force works 9-5 and lives in the States, and they'll honor the agreement and leave the mob up for me.<br>
<br>
    Personally, I agree with that after 24 hours it passes to the next guild.  Exceptions being if per RTA you cannot zone into fear; there's an uniamous agreement by all members on the rotation; server connectivity and stability are giving you a rogering.<br>
